## E — Map Tech: Confirmed Working Patterns (from live source read of MapView.jsx)

**Tile URL (exact, confirmed working):**
```
https://{s}.basemaps.cartocdn.com/rastertiles/voyager/{z}/{x}/{y}{r}.png
```
Attribution: `&copy; <a href="https://www.openstreetmap.org/copyright">OpenStreetMap</a> contributors &copy; <a href="https://carto.com/attributions">CARTO</a>`

**Init pattern (StrictMode-safe, confirmed):**
```js
useEffect(() => {
  if (leafletRef.current) return;
  const map = L.map('map-container', { center: [25, 12], zoom: 3, zoomControl: true });
  L.tileLayer(TILE_URL, { attribution: TILE_ATTR, maxZoom: 19 }).addTo(map);
  map.zoomControl.setPosition('bottomright');
  leafletRef.current = map;
  return () => { map.remove(); leafletRef.current = null; };
}, []);
```
Start at `zoom: 3` (not 2) — shows global spread clearly without world-repeat tiles.

**Price-pin DivIcon (from pre-researcher §E, carry forward exactly):**
```js
const createPricePin = (price, active = false) => L.divIcon({
  className: '',
  html: `<div style="background:${active ? '#B8975A' : '#12100E'};color:#fff;
         font-family:'DM Sans',sans-serif;font-size:11px;font-weight:600;
         padding:4px 8px;border-radius:3px;white-space:nowrap;
         box-shadow:0 2px 6px rgba(0,0,0,0.3);letter-spacing:0.02em">${price}</div>`,
  iconSize: [null, null], iconAnchor: [0, 0]
});
```

**Marker sync pattern (from live App.jsx + MapView.jsx read):**
- `selectedProperty` state in App.jsx; passed as prop to both `<MapView>` and `<PropertyList>`
- `onSelectProperty` callback triggers `map.flyTo([lat, lng], 13, { duration: 0.8 })`; also update all pin icons via `markers.forEach(m => m.setIcon(createPricePin(price, m._propId === id)))`
- List scrolls selected card into view: `cardRef.current?.scrollIntoView({ behavior: 'smooth', block: 'nearest' })`
- `markersRef.current` = object keyed by property id (same pattern as mn-state-park-tracker)

**Critical gotcha confirmed from source:** Must `import 'leaflet/dist/leaflet.css'` at top of MapView.jsx. `L.divIcon` requires `className: ''`. Both confirmed working in scaffold.

