## H — App Architecture (state-only, no routing)

**View state in App.jsx:**
```js
const [view, setView] = useState('browse');         // 'browse' | 'favorites'
const [selectedProperty, setSelectedProperty] = useState(null);
const [detailOpen, setDetailOpen] = useState(false);
const [favorites, setFavorites] = useState(() => {
  try { return JSON.parse(localStorage.getItem('ks_favorites') || '[]'); } catch { return []; }
});
```

**Favorites persist:**
```js
useEffect(() => {
  localStorage.setItem('ks_favorites', JSON.stringify(favorites));
}, [favorites]);
```

**Mobile layout:** Split-pane stacks (map on top, list below) below 768px. Filter panel collapses to a floating "Filters" button. Detail modal goes full-screen. Navbar shows burger menu. CEO mandate: build and QA this.

